t - finding the places it describes on a map, or arriving at a conclusion about the social reality experienced by a historical community of redactors. These utopian goals are projected onto a utopian text. This volume advocates an honest hermeneutical approach to the question of how reliably a past reality can be reconstructed from a biblical passage, and it aims to provide an example of disclosing - not obscuring - pre-suppositions brought to the text.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Nov 2019) 0aReligion and geography. 4aAltes Testament. 4aBibelrezeption. 4aHebrew Bible. 4aHermeneutik. 4aUtopie. 4ahermeneutics. 4ascience fiction. 4autopia. 70(DE-601)1045985490(DE-588)4054021-2aScience-Fiction-Literatur2gnd 70(DE-601)1062199600(DE-588)4041251-9aUtopie2gnd 70(DE-601)82056138X0(DE-588)1068651520aGelobtes LandgMotiv2gnd 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2015z9783110438727oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831104142710 cprintz978311041154640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110414172423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110414172.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aZDB-23-DGFb2015  aZDB-23-DGGb2015